title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.27. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <i>plural</i>, = Latin <i>regiones caeli</i>, <b>fields</b> into which the Augurs divided the <b>templum</b> of the heavens, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Camillus” 32, “Rom.” 22. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> <b>squares</b> or <b>checks</b> of tartan, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.30. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.5</b></Level3> <b>front frame</b> of a torsion-engine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 60.6, 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Belopoeica” 81.10 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>case</b> or <b>chamber</b> in which mechanism is fitted, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aut.” 5.3. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.6</b></Level3> generally, <b>rectangle,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 2.5.36, “PMag.Lond.” 46.349,361. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8819","accentedUnicode":"πλινθίον","shortDef":"a brick-kiln","mediumDef":"a brick-kiln","stepGloss":"a brick-kiln","stepTransliteration":"plinthion","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}